<item>
<title>Nigeria: Nigeria: Severe Local Storms - May 2017</title>
<link>http://reliefweb.int/disaster/st-2017-000063-nga</link>
<description>GLIDE number: ST-2017-000063-NGA&lt;br/&gt;
Disaster type: Severe Local Storm&lt;br/&gt;
Affected countries: Nigeria&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A storm in Maiduguri, on May 6, caused significant damage in 27 IDP camps, destroying around 362 shelters and partially damaging around 831 shelters, 26 latrines blocks and 114 education facilities (108 in Borno and 6 in Yobe). With the onset of the rainy season a flood vulnerability mapping was carried out in the IDP camps in Borno and an estimated 59 IDP camps (out of 164) are at risk of flooding, potentially affecting 70,5862 households (328,000 persons), including 66,000 children under five. The shelter and camp coordination sector is working on drainage issues in camps and UNICEF is prepositioning dewatering pumps to sites with high risk of water-logging.(&lt;a href=&quot;http://reliefweb.int/report/nigeria/nigeria-humanitarian-sitrep-no-9-1-15-may-2017&quot;&gt;UNICEF, 15 May 2017&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As an immediate response to a storm on 2 June 2017, the International Organization for Migration (IOM) Nigeria carried out a rapid assessment of camps and camp-like settings in Jere, Kaga, Konduga and Maiduguri Metropolitan Council (MMC) between 2 and 3 June to assess the level of damage sustained to the structures. Out of the 44 camps assessed, eight sustained damages of varying degrees, while the remaining were unaffected. One fatality was recorded in Bakasi Camp. In addition to the damage to the shelters, some parts of the camps were flooded. (&lt;a href=&quot;http://reliefweb.int/report/nigeria/iom-rapid-assessment-nigeria-flash-report-storm-damage-idps-sites-3-june-2017&quot;&gt;IOM, 3 Jun 2017&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Date: 06 May 2017&lt;br/&gt;
Status: Alert</description>
<guid isPermaLink="false">http://reliefweb.int/disaster/st-2017-000063-nga</guid>
<pubDate>Sat, 06 May 2017 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
<source url="http://reliefweb.int/disasters/rss.xml">ReliefWeb Disasters</source>
